## Build approach

Read these in order:
1. `ROADMAP.md` — phased build plan
2. `workflows/<id>.md` — what each workflow does (one file per workflow)
3. `agents/<id>/` — CrewAI-shaped agent designs (one folder per agent)
4. `integrations/INVENTORY.md` — tier-ranked tools
5. `governance/` — safety contracts
6. `runtime/BUILD.md` — build plan for the runtime substrate

## Conventions

### Subagents

Each agent in `agents/<id>/` may be implemented as a Claude Code subagent
in `.claude/agents/<id>.md` (recommended for `full` autonomy agents) or
as a `claude -p` invocation pattern (recommended for `semi`/`supervised`
agents that need approval gating). The reference impl's `wake.sh` does
the latter.

### Skills

If your team has cross-cutting capabilities, package them as Claude Code
skills under `.claude/skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md`. The `mcp-builder`
skill (for `NEEDS-MCP-WRAPPER` integrations) is one example you'll
likely need.

### Hooks

The reference impl ships `hooks/autonomy-gate.sh` (PreToolUse blast-radius
blocker). Register via `.claude/settings.local.json`:

```json
{
  "hooks": {
    "PreToolUse": [
      {"matcher": ".*", "hooks": [{"type": "command", "command": "$REPO_ROOT/hooks/autonomy-gate.sh"}]}
    ]
  }
}
```

This hook blocks side-effect tools (L3+) when the agent's autonomy is
`semi`/`supervised` and there's no matching `/approve` record in
`.agentbloc/state/approvals.jsonl`.

### MCP servers

`integrations/existing/<tool>.md` lists already-deployed MCPs. Install
each + add to `.mcp.json`:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "<tool>": { "command": "...", "args": [...] }
  }
}
```

For `NEEDS-MCP-WRAPPER` tools, run `/mcp-build` per
`integrations/needs-mcp-wrapper/<tool>/BUILD.md`.

## Runtime — bash + cron + Telegram (default)

If you use the reference impl in `runtime/reference-impl/`:

1. `cp runtime/reference-impl/.env.example .env` and fill in
   `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN`, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`
2. `./runtime/reference-impl/cron-generator.sh apply` to install crontab
   (or set `AGENTBLOC_NO_CRON=1` and use `./runtime/reference-impl/loop.sh`
   for foreground operation)
3. The cron lines fire `wake.sh <agent-id>` per agent's schedule;
   `claude-wrap.sh` invokes `claude -p` with the agent's `wake.md`

If you pick a different runtime (n8n, Temporal, Pipedream, Inngest,
custom Python), see `runtime/alternatives.md` for tradeoffs and adapt
the contract from the bash impl.

## Testing

Each workflow in `workflows/<id>.md` ships falsifiable success criteria.
Implement them as integration tests against your runtime of choice.

`governance/audit-trail.md` defines the JSONL schema your audit
implementation must match — assert on shape in tests.

